=======================================================================

%^RED%^%^BOLD%^ SYNTAX :: %^RESET%^ set_listen ( target, message )
%^RED%^%^BOLD%^ SYNTAX :: %^RESET%^ set_listen ( target, function )

This function is present in all objects. It will add the listen named
in the string target into the object. Either a string message can be
defined or a function pointer (: :) .

see also ::

set_listens, remove_listen, remove_listens, query_listen, query_listens

